,"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"Brother and husband both married Fenn sisters","body":"Her brother Samuel Newton married Martha Fenn in 1669. Her second husband Samuel Burwell had previously been married to Sarah Fenn — Martha's sister, same parents. Two Newton siblings married into the same Fenn family, though into different branches of it."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Father left her his three hour-glasses","body":"Because Susannah had already received her portion at marriage, Roger Newton Sr.'s 1683 will left her only one cow and all three of his hour-glasses. She was living in Guilford with five children at the time. The genealogical note adds dryly: 'No one can tell why she should have all the hour-glasses.'"},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Two marriages, six children, two Connecticut towns","body":"She had four children with her first husband John Stone, then married Samuel Burwell as his second wife. She was living in Guilford with five children when her father's 1683 will was written, then moved to Milford with the Burwells. She died at Milford in July 1703, age 48."}],"quotes":[],"research_sources":[],"artworks":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Susannah Newton Burwell","first_name":"Susannah","last_name":"Burwell","married_names":["Stone","Burwell"],"maiden_name":"Newton"},"documents":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"susannah-burwell-1654"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}